summary: In a dominant performance on Sunday Night Football, the Philadelphia Eagles defeated the Los Angeles Rams 37-20, extending their winning streak to seven games. Eagles running back Saquon Barkley had a historic night, setting a franchise record with 255 rushing yards. Barkley also contributed two touchdowns and 47 receiving yards, totaling 302 yards of offense. His impressive reverse hurdle drew attention on social media and was even featured in the Madden 25 video game. The Eagles' victory was a statement win, solidifying their position as contenders in the NFC. Barkley's performance earned praise from fans and analysts alike, with many hailing it as one of the best rushing performances in recent memory.
